%C A075648 From _Christian Wolird_, Jul 22 2026: (Start)
%C A075648 A growth rate of O(n^3 / log n) is indicated (though not proven) from a suitable probabilistic approximation.
%C A075648 The sequence is not strictly increasing: a(28) = 727 < 947 = a(27).
%C A075648 Consecutive terms appear surprisingly far into the sequence. For example, a(14514) = 71887645623 and a(14513) = 71887645622.
%C A075648 The frontier terms of the sequence oddly split into two distinct bands around the 15000th term. (End)
